<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,798,1149]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
This species is unique within the Ophiderini as the only species with an oblique reddish pink hindwing patch conspicuous against a black background. We include specimen records from 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1091,907,933]" name="Venezuela" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1146,1315,907,933]" name="French Guiana" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, and a live image from 
<collectingCountry box="[286,341,943,969]" name="Peru" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Peru</collectingCountry>
. It has also been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[691,812,943,969]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schaus, W." box="[826,984,943,970]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="173 - 193" refId="ref40161" refString="Schaus, W. (1911 b) New species of Heterocera from Costa Rica - IV. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 8, 7 (38), 173 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931108692920" type="journal article" year="1911">Schaus 1911b</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1044,1112,943,969]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Felder, C. &amp; Felder, R. &amp; Rogenhofer, A. F." box="[1125,1428,943,969]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref37356" refString="Felder, C., Felder, R. &amp; Rogenhofer, A. F. (1874) Atlas der Heterocera Sphingida-Noctuida. Heft 4. In: Felder, C., Felder, R. &amp; Rogenhofer, A. F. (Eds.), ([&quot; 1864 &quot;] 1865 - 1875), Reise der Osterreichischen Fregatte Novara um die Erde in den Jahren 1857, 1858, 1859 unter den Befehlen des Commodore B. Von Wullerstorf-Urbair Zoologischer Theil. Zweiter Band. Zweite Abtheilung. Lepidoptera. Hof-und Staatsdruckerei, Vienna, pls. 108 - 120." type="journal volume" year="1874">Felder &amp; Rogenhofer 1874</bibRefCitation>
) in addition to the 
<typeStatus box="[349,397,979,1005]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingCountry box="[500,610,979,1005]" name="Colombia" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[627,788,979,1006]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="181 - 199" refId="ref41093" refString="Walker, F. (1867 b) Characters of undescribed heterocerous Lepidoptera. Journal of the Proceedings of the Linnean Society, 9, 181 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1867. tb 00191. x" type="journal article" year="1867">Walker 1867b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,798,1149]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
In 1867 Walker described the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1867" box="[617,702,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Tetrisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[617,702,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Tetrisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in two separate publications, one for Hemiptera (
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[1270,1429,1015,1042]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref41042" refString="Walker, F. (1867 a) Catalogue of the specimens of heteropterous-Hemiptera in the collection of the British Museum. Vol. 1. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 240 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 118688" type="book" year="1867">Walker 1867a</bibRefCitation>
) and one for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker 1867 b)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[295,622,1051,1078]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">
Lepidoptera (
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[449,614,1051,1078]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="181 - 199" refId="ref41093" refString="Walker, F. (1867 b) Characters of undescribed heterocerous Lepidoptera. Journal of the Proceedings of the Linnean Society, 9, 181 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1867. tb 00191. x" type="journal article" year="1867">Walker 1867b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The Hemiptera genus name was published nearly four months before the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[194,329,1087,1113]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
genus. Therefore, a replacement genus name is required for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Waldkircher et al. 2004)" baseAuthorityName="Waldkircher" baseAuthorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Tetrisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florigera">
<emphasis box="[1022,1215,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Tetrisia florigera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Waldkircher, G. &amp; Webb, M. D. &amp; Maschwitz, U." pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="21 - 28" refId="ref40924" refString="Waldkircher, G., Webb, M. D. &amp; Maschwitz, U. (2004) Description of a new shieldbug (Heteroptera: Plataspidae) and its close association with a species of ant (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Southeast Asia. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 147 (1), 21 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 22119434 - 900000133" type="journal article" year="2004">
Waldkircher 
<emphasis box="[1379,1429,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
